				</div>

			</div>

		
			<div class="post-3922 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized tag-business tag-economy tag-government tag-politics tag-vacation">

				<div class="entry">

					<h2><a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/2012/06/28/college-subprime-loans-the-next-bubble-ready-to-pop/">College subprime loans: the next bubble ready to&nbsp;pop</a></h2>

					<div class="post-info">
						<p>
							<span class="time">June 28, 2012</span>
															<span class="author">by <a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/author/mktgeistmike/" title="Posts by mktgeistmike" rel="author">mktgeistmike</a></span>
																						<span class="post-comments"><a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/2012/06/28/college-subprime-loans-the-next-bubble-ready-to-pop/#respond" title="Comment on College subprime loans: the next bubble ready to&nbsp;pop">Leave a comment</a></span>
																				</p>
					</div>

					<p>If no bank will lend your kid $100,000 to get a degree in sociology without the feds promising to assume all risk, there&#8217;s a reason: In 4 years, your kid will have the same job prospects he does now but will have $100,000 in debt and no way to pay it off. And colleges keep on jacking up prices because the federal gravy train keeps rolling. Subprime loans: When will we learn?</p>
<p><a href="http://mktgeist.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/582122_10151004887724872_378329174_n.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3923" title="582122_10151004887724872_378329174_n" src="http://mktgeist.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/582122_10151004887724872_378329174_n.jpg?w=630" alt=""   /></a></p>
<div class="clear"></div>

				</div>

				<div class="post-meta">
					<p>
						<span class="categories">Filed under <a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/category/uncategorized/" rel="category tag">Uncategorized</a></span>
						<span class="tags">Tagged with <a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/tag/business/" rel="tag">business</a>, <a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/tag/economy/" rel="tag">Economy</a>, <a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/tag/government/" rel="tag">GOVERNMENT</a>, <a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/tag/politics/" rel="tag">politics</a>, <a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/tag/vacation/" rel="tag">vacation</a></span>					</p>
				</div>

